InvalidOperationException is a runtime error thrown when the current state of an object is not suitable to execute the called method or operation. 
The most critical word here is the concept of "state".

InvalidOperationException gives your software the following message: "I know how to do
what you are asking of me (the method is valid), there is no problem with the data you gave me
either (the parameters are valid), but my current condition/state is not suitable to perform this task."

int sayi = null;

// WRONG USAGE: The system throws an InvalidOperationException here.
int sonuc = sayi.Value;
